# Problem statement:
The web team wants a solution to improve the reliability of their beach wave conditions page.

# Solution Request:
Improve website reliability by migrating to Amazon S3 static website hosting.

# Project Summary:
This project demonstrates how to host a static website on Amazon S3, improve availability by leveraging AWS’s durable storage service, and apply proper security practices when exposing a public website.

# Services used:
Amazon S3
•	Hosted the static website
•	Managed file uploads and object permissions
•	Configured bucket policy for public website access

# In this lab, I completed the following tasks:
•	Enabled static website hosting on an Amazon S3 bucket.
•	Configured and reviewed the bucket policy to ensure secure public access for website files.
•	Uploaded website assets and validated that the site loads successfully via the S3 website endpoint.
•	Renamed index.html to waves.html as part of the custom task.

